data.meta_description: Duke Karl-Theodor in Bavaria ( 1839 – 1909) was a member of the House of Wittelsbach & a professional oculist. He was the brother of the Empress Elisabeth of Austria. Karl-Theodor was born at Possenhofen Castle, the third son of Duke Maximilian in Bavaria & of his wife, Princess Ludovika of Bavaria. On 11 February 1865, at Dresden, Karl-Theodor married his first cousin Princess Sophie of Saxony (1845–1867), daughter of King John of Saxony & his maternal aunt Princess Amalie Auguste of Bavaria.
